                </div><h3 style="text-align: justify;"><span id="1_Hau_qua_cua_thiet_hai_vat_chat_xe_o_to"><span style="color: #ed1c24; font-size: 100%;">1. Consequences of physical damage to cars</span></span></h3><p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 100%; color: #000000;">A car accident can ruin a day or more of your work. In addition to the inconvenience of having to cancel work plans or an appointment, you also have to deal with car damage, costs, and even injuries.</span></p><p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 100%; color: #000000;">Most car drivers are often involved in at least once in their life an accident, whether minor or major. You may be driving very carefully, but that doesn't save you from people driving while staring at their phone screens to text someone, resulting in careless drivers on the road. The road has actively crashed into your car and the accident is obvious. In fact, even you yourself may have had times when distracted, distracted while driving, and if unfortunately, the accident happened is not difficult to understand. The distraction while driving can come from many different causes, the most common and common causes can be seen as: </span></p><p style="text-align: justify;">
